    "body": "There's more than one performance offenders. First is the `StackView` used in the wallet view. It's creating all the wallet tabs/views when the active section is changed to wallet. The `Collectibles` tab is the heaviest one. Currently all the collectibles are being loaded once the `Collectibles` tab is created. Another perf offender is the custom `SortFilterProxyModel` created for the `Collectibles` tab. We're fetching the settings for the collectibles sort/filter and apply the rules to a custom `SortFilterProxyModel`. It takes a few seconds to properly set-up a model with a few thousand collectibles.\r\n\r\nIn order to fix this issue we need to firstly fix the unrolled grid views to fix the memory bomb. Afterwards we need to remove the `StackView` and use a lazy loading mechanism for the wallet internal pages/tabs. At this step the wallet should be quite responsive (at least when it's being opened). And it will be fast for most users.\r\n\r\nNice to have: Improve the `Collectibles` performance issues introduced by the new proxies.\r\n\r\nTODO:\r\n\r\n- [ ] https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/issues/13027 - This task is needed before switching from `StackView` to `Loaders` (or any other lazy load approach).\r\n- [ ] https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/issues/13165 - This task will should be fixed by https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/issues/13045\r\n- [ ] Go back to the lazy load approach for the wallet pages and replace `StackView` with `Loaders`",
